==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sesquialterate
<hw>Ses`qui*al"ter*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sesquialter</ets> once and a half; <ets>sesqui-</ets> +
<ets>alter</ets> other: cf. F. <ets>sesquialt⟦eacute⟧re</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Once and a half times as great as another; having the ratio of one
and a half to one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sesquialteral ratio</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>the
ratio of one and a half to one; <as>thus, 9 and 6 are in a
<ex>sesquialteral ratio</ex></as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesquialterous</ent>⟦br⟧
